Package: fsuite
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, bash (>= 4.0), coreutils, findutils, perl, sqlite3
Recommends: tree, ripgrep, fd-find, python3
Description: Filesystem investigation toolkit for humans and AI agents
 fsuite provides a suite-level help command plus nine composable CLI
 tools that turn filesystem reconnaissance, continuity, and editing into
 a clean, scriptable, agent-friendly pipeline:
 .
  * fsuite - Show the conceptual workflow and suite-level guidance
  * fsearch - Find files by name, extension, or glob pattern
  * fcontent - Search inside files for text (powered by ripgrep)
  * ftree - Visualize directory structure with smart defaults and recon mode
  * fmap - Extract structural skeleton of code files (code cartography)
  * fread - Read files with budgets, context windows, and diff-aware ranges
  * fcase - Preserve investigation state and hand off the live case cleanly
  * fedit - Apply surgical text patches with batch mode, symbol shortcuts, and dry-run diffs
  * freplay - Record and replay derivation paths for investigation reproducibility
  * fmetrics - Analyze local telemetry and predict runtime
 .
 The reconnaissance tools output in multiple formats (pretty, paths,
 JSON) for both human and programmatic consumption. The continuity layer
 keeps targets, evidence, and handoffs structured, while fmetrics
 provides telemetry analytics for performance tracking.
